d the Gabba rebuild be scrapped in favour of a $3.4 billion stadium to be built in a corner of inner-city Victoria Park, which was being repurposed from a golf course to public green space.\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Gabba\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.140713164573612e-17, \"text\": \"Gabba\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Gabba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Gabba\"}, {\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electoral_district_of_Victoria_Park\", \"score\": 0.9999999935680535, \"rank\": 5.28873841153222e-09, \"text\": \"Victoria Park\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electoral_district_of_Victoria_Park\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electoral_district_of_Victoria_Park\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"favour\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2453}, {\"ngram\": \"a $3.4 billion stadium\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2479}, {\"ngram\": \"a corner\", \"from\": 2495, \"to\": 2503}, {\"ngram\": \"a golf course\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2578}, {\"ngram\": \"public green space\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2600}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Miles rejected that recommendation and instead announcedQSAC would host Olympic and Paralympic track and field events.\", \"from\": 2603, \"to\": 2725, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Miles\", \"from\": 2607, \"to\": 2612}, {\"ngram\": \"that recommendation\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2641}, {\"ngram\": \"instead announcedQSAC\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2667}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic and Paralympic track and field events\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2724}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The stadium would hold just 40,000 people during the Games - the smallest Olympic capacity since Amsterdam 1928 - with permanent seating for just 14,000 post-2032.\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2823, \"end\": 2837, \"